            <fr:title text="The univalence principle for types">The univalence principle for types</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001D.agda" type="external">erct-001D.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-004B.xml" title="Reflexive graph" addr="//erct/erct-004B" type="local">reflexive graph</fr:link> structure on types given by <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="//erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalences</fr:link> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0010.xml" title="Path object" addr="//erct/erct-0010" type="local">univalent</fr:link>. We shall write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {Type}]]></fr:tex> to indicate the resulting (large) path object of types and <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000V.xml" title="Equivalence of types" addr="//erct/erct-000V" type="local">equivalences</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
