            <fr:title text="Isomorphism of precategories">Isomorphism of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000B.xml" title="Precategory" addr="//erct/erct-000B" type="local">precategories</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000J.agda" type="external">erct-000J.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000I.xml" title="Functor between precategories" addr="//erct/erct-000I" type="local">functor</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F\colon  C \to  D]]></fr:tex> is called an <fr:em><fr:strong>isomorphism</fr:strong></fr:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  C\cong  D]]></fr:tex>, when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-000K.xml" title="Full and faithful functor" addr="//erct/erct-000K" type="local">fully faithful</fr:link> and its action on objects is an equivalence of types.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Being an isomorphism is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>3</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>19327</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">//erct/erct-000B</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>foreign-erct-erct-000B.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Precategory">Precategory</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000B.agda" type="external">erct-000B.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>precategory</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex> is specified by the following data:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>a type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lvert C\right \rvert \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> of <fr:em>objects</fr:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  C]]></fr:tex> a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001J.xml" title="Sets" addr="//erct/erct-001J" type="local">set</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex> of <fr:em>arrows</fr:em>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x\to  y]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  C]]></fr:tex>, an <fr:em>identity arrow</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{x}\colon  x\to  x]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  x\to  y]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  y\to  z]]></fr:tex>, a <fr:em>composite arrow</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  x \to  z]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
  <fr:li>such that composition is associative and unital with respect to identity arrows:
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \boldsymbol {\lambda }_{f}\colon  1_{y}\circ  f = f\quad 
      \boldsymbol {\rho }_{f}\colon  f\circ  1_{x} = f \quad 
      \boldsymbol {\alpha }_{f,g,h}\colon  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h\circ  g\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\circ  f = h\circ 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen g\circ  f\right \rparen \mathclose {}

    ]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
